gere und gegenwärtige Positionen von Denkern wie Adorno, Benjamin und Derrida berücksichtigt.  aModernity is shaped by a particular configuration between subjectivity and art. But how exactly can this be grasped? This volume pursues this question with the use of a deconstructive interpretation of the texts of Hegel and Nietzsche.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aDerrida. 4aDeutsche Philosophiegeschichte. 4aEntsubjektivierung. 4aHegel. 4aKulturphilosophie. 4aKunst. 4aNietzsche. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPhilosophiegeschichte. 4aSubjektivität. 4aTheodor W. Adorno. 4aWalter Benjamin. 4aÄsthetik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aArt.  aDerrida.  aGerman History of Philosophy.  aHegel.  aHistory of Philosophy.  aNietzsche.  aPhilosophy of Culture.  aPhilosophy.  aSubjectivity.  aTheodor W. Adorno.  aWalter Benjamin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2017z9783110548228oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839436110zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839436110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839436110/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPHb2017